title: Last Call with Richard Crouse
description:
Last Call is a podcast on the stories behind the places where everybody knows your name. It's a chance to soak up the ambiance of the world's greatest watering holes without leaving your home.

I’m Richard Crouse. I tended bar for seventeen years everywhere from hot spots to dive bars and I thought I had seen it all.

In my life behind bars I witnessed everything from first dates and marriage proposals to knife fights and a woman who brought a pet monkey in for a drink.

Nothing could surprise me.

Or so I thought.

Then I heard about how a lion who visited Harry’s New York Bar in Paris inspired Ernest Hemingway to write one of his greatest novels. And why there are century old chicken bones hanging above the beer-stained bar at McSorleys in New York City. And how Vincent Sardi refused to do business with the mob during Prohibition, so his famous Broadway Restaurant didn’t serve alcohol until the 21st amendment passed, six year after they first opened.

With the help of the Last Call radio players, music and interviews with cocktail detectives Jared Brown and Anistatia Miller, The Indiana Jones of Tiki, Jeff “Beachbum” Berry and Two and Two: McSorley's, My Dad, and Me author Rafe Bartholomew, I bring these stories, and many more, to life in my podcast Last Call. It’s fact folded in with a sprinkling of fiction, because, well, who doesn’t exaggerate after a few drinks?

So, open that bottle of wine or crack that beer and join me for an intoxicating guided tour of some of the strange stories from some of the world’s best boozers.

Brought to you by Television's Senior News Anchor Timothy Marbun.

This podcast takes you to talk about the latest going on in Jakarta and Indonesia from an Indonesian perspective, all performed in english. Dwell into a vast selection of topics, ranging from Pop-Culture, Digital Trends, up to Money and Business Opportunities by hearing it from the perspective of a seasoned journalist, and through talks with various interesting personalities found throughout Jakarta and beyond.

Tim has been a News Anchor and Broadcast Journalist for 15 years, and has reported major news events including National Elections, Social unrest in Thailand, Human Trafficking in Malaysia, and Massive Protests during the Arab Spring. Notable interviews include Palestinian PM, Twitter CEO, Instagram CEO, Coldplay, and Ed Sheeran.

Jakarta has been his home for the last 3 decades, after moving in from Norman Oklahoma where he spent part of his childhood. 

Tim also regularly moderates International events and seminars, including the IMF-World Bank Annual Meeting, Bali Democracy Forum, Indonesia-Africa Infrastructure Dialogue, and many more.

title: Raw Vegan Lens
description: Join me for an authentic raw vegan journey. I will never sugar coat my experience, lol. If you're searching for a pristine, flawless, skyrocket to raw perfection, keep searching. This is not it. My raw journey resembles a big pile of knotted zoodles. I bought my first raw book, Juliano's RAW in 2000. In 2006, I finally realized that raw a was an actual lifestyle, not just a handful of freakishly disciplined people, and I started 'going raw.' I've gone raw and fallen down literally hundreds of times. But I'm always learning and honing my skills. I will not stop. I can't. There's nothing like raw. I believe it's the absolute best version of myself, hands down, the person I was meant to be. How can you discover your full potential, if you're not using the best fuel and becoming your best self? Raw veganism is an incredibly healing path. It's also the way I choose to manage my ADHD and the most effective way I've discovered since being diagnosed at age 6. In 2005 at hypnotherapy school, I experienced a powerful dream, did dream a therapy session on myself and developed an obsession with self healing. Off the top of my head, I've healed uterine fibroids, squamous skin cancers, UTIs, sinus infections, plantar fasciitis, bronchitis and most recently an undetermined autoimmune illness. Join me for an honest look at a raw path and growth.

title: Bucket List Traveller
description:
I’m on a crazy journey to achieving my biggest life goal of living in 7 countries! Crazy?  Perhaps! I moved to New Zealand (country number 4), during the pandemic, with my husband, beautiful 4 year old daughter and our gorgeous black Labrador. 

I’m here to share my story, the ups and downs of my journey so far, the tips & tricks I have learnt along the way, and interviews with friends smashing out their own bucket lists, with the hope our stories and journeys can inspire you to make a plan to achieve your bucket lists whatever they may look like ... so all those “maybe one day” things become “I can’t believe I did it” things…

For me, the meaning of life is the collection of experiences we accumulate along the way and the incredible people we meet. Life is a journey, not a destination… it shouldn’t be about the “one day”, it should be about the everyday, about the experiences - so make the journey fun!

Yes you only live once, BUT you only die once, and you get the chance to live every single day!

So my question is… what’s stopping you from living the life you truly want and chasing YOUR bucket list dreams?

description: A tale of two best friends who couldn't be more opposite in their looks, style and how we operate in life. But know too much about one another to let each another get away. She started as a teen Mom who attended beauty school as a start her intro into adulthood. Which is where she met a fellow teen Mom Samantha who is now a dark haired gypsy, thriving blogger, emotional support coach and single mother of 2. Little did we know we would meet each other during a time of growth, hardships and misfortune. Over 15 years later these Twisted Sisters have overcame failed relationships, solo parenting, poverty, starting businesses from scratch, marriage and overcoming debt. To defying near death illness, navigating the business world at a young age, becoming a widow to suicide and learning how to follow our passions/dreams despite certain challenges. In our battle through life we have made some wonderful connections and relationships with some very prominent people. We are thrilled that we get to share these beautiful souls with all of you and discuss the various impacts in their lives which in turn helped lead them into success and happiness. Follow these Twisted sisters as they believe despite certain hardships, you can't take life too seriously, imperfection is beauty and it's better to be absolutely ridiculous than absolutely boring.

description:
New episodes every Thursday! 

cornrc.com

In the 1980s, Culture was being shaped by immerging digital video technology.  Tony Wannamaker was one of the founders of Much Music “The Nation's Music Station”. The  messages playing out in music videos. Being a blue-collar cameraman gave Tony the ability to access and document this cultural revolution through the camera lens while adding to the cultural shift itself through his visual reporting.  
As Pat Canavan interviews Tony about his 40-year career, the podcast delves into the Canadian identity in pop culture outside of the US narrative. We get an inside look at Tony's adventures around the world, including encounters with celebrities like Sidney Poitier, musicians David Bowie, The Rolling Stones, Madonna, Lenny Kravitz and more. title: Venice Talks
description:
Venice Talks is a podcast series about Venice in Italy, hosted by Monica Cesarato, who is putting her insider experience at your disposal to help you experience the city at 360 !

There is a reason why Venice is one of the most visited cities in the world: is it perhaps because its attractions are something absolutely unique? Absolutely so. Nowhere else will you find a city built entirely on water with a glorious history spanning centuries.

Bu there are two ways to visit Venice: following the rush of tourists who in a few hours drag themselves along a predetermined route chosen by about 20 million people every year, or leaving this path trying to discover a less postcard-worthy Venice.

I think you can do both: you can go and enjoy Saint Marks’ Square and its monument or the Rialto Bridge admiring the Grand Canal, fighting though with the crowds to be able to take a souvenir photo.

But you can also get out of the cliché about Venice and discover that there are extraordinary places even in a city that in itself is out of any ordinary. Venice is not just about its monuments and its history: it’s about its people, the Venetians.

So,if you are planning your vacation, or it is already organized but you are looking for more useful tips for visiting Venice, you are on the right place.

This is a weekly podcast on the Venetian people, their lives and struggles in the city of Venice.

Every week, Venice Talks aims to find what’s going on among the canals and small alleyways, uncovering the stories and speaking to the people that matter. These conversations aim to animate, educate and create discussions about how to visit Venice the right and sustainable way. We do this through sharing fascinating stories about the past, present and future of Venice. This podcast is a cultural platform to discuss the most salient issues facing our city today and celebrate the people, organisations and stories behind The Serenissima.

description:
What is the High Life Uncut? 

The high Life Uncut is a podcast that discusses the lives of those that work in what is dubbed as Syd,Aus and/or Australia’s ‘Top Tier’ corporates. 


Who are the Podcast hosts Jen & Alex? 

Jen & Alex are Gen Z 9-5 corporates in a ‘Top Tier’ Australian bank. They are ambitious corporates who have combined 10-12 years experience across professional services, tourism, start-up, tech, fast moving consumer goods (fmcg) and financial services. 


Why The High Life Uncut? 

Jen & Alex realised there are conversations that we are afraid to strike up at times outside of the workplace or even with close friends. 

They talk through topics that can be uncomfortable to discuss from a male and female perspective. 

It’s about the fine art of balance between your personal life blurring into your career. 

Grab yourself a beveragino and find a spot to kick back so you can listen to The High Life Uncut.

Sobre nosotros:
Miryam(Miry) es de la Ciudad de México y vivió en México hasta 2019 antes de mudarse a Alemania. Estudió mercadotecnia en la Universidad Motolínea del Pedregal, maquillaje en la London Academy of Freelance Makeup y en el corto plazo "la danza como profesión" en Danceworks Berlín. Ahora trabaja como empleada en Berlín y busca nuevos retos.

Jonathan (Johnny) nació en Berlín y está a punto de terminar su licenciatura en guitarra de jazz en la Hochschule für Musik Dresden. Pronto le gustaría hacer un máster en composición o guitarra de jazz. Sus grandes pasiones, además de la música, son el club de fútbol 1.FC Union Berlin y el surf de olas. Trabaja de forma independiente como profesor de música y guitarra.

Ambos se conocieron en la preparatoria en Ciudad de México en 2011 cuando tenían 15 y 16 años respectivamente y han logrado mantener vivo su amor hasta hoy.

Comida, música, ocio, actividad, sociedad... ¡Estamos aquí para hablar de todo esto y más! Somos Andrea y María, y somos novias separadas por ocho horas de diferencia horaria: ¡Seúl - Madrid! Venimos a contaros nuestra historia de Culture Shock en Corea; la primera vez que pisamos Corea del Sur, cómo fue para Andrea vivir allí un tiempo, y cómo está siendo para nosotras estar long-distance mientras que Andrea está en Seúl, y María se queda en Madrid. ¿Qué cosas nos siguen chocando pase el tiempo que pase? ¿Qué cosas no te puedes perder en el país? ¿Qué cosas extrañas nos han pasado? Episodes will generally be about 45-60 minutes in length, covering everything from nearby lodging and food to all the park's amenities, of course including a long discussion of trails and hiking in the park. 

Whether you're looking for somewhere with family fun, history, backpacking, vast overlooks, or a combination, you're bound to find your next destination right here, on Nature's Finest. 1-2 new episodes per month!

My aim is to be a great resource on places to visit and escape the fluorescent lights or city noise, but this is an entertainment show, and you should contact real pros, like a Ranger's Office, for example, and be sure to do your own homework before tackling a new destination. There's no such thing as too much research when it comes to Mother Nature. Always take notice of posted recreation rules and recommendations wherever you go.

title: Cultural Connections Lab
description:
Welcome to Cultural Connections Lab, a podcast that explores the intersections of culture, travel, education, and language learning. We believe that learning about other cultures can be a transformative experience that broadens our understanding of the world, breaks down barriers, and promotes empathy and respect for diverse perspectives. Each episode, we take a deep dive into a different cultural topic, sharing stories and insights from experts and everyday people who have experienced it firsthand. Our hosts, Dr. J. Taylor Tribble, Dr. Kelly Forbes, and Mike Overholt come from diverse backgrounds and bring their own unique perspectives to the table. From seasoned travelers to language enthusiasts, our team is passionate about exploring new cultures and sharing their knowledge with others. Whether you're a seasoned traveler or just starting out on your cultural jouney, Cultural Connections Lab (CCL) has something for you. Join us as we explore the world and make meaningful connections across cultures.

title: Life Beyond Borders
description:
Welkom bij Life Beyond Borders, de podcast waarin we de verhalen ontdekken van Belgen en Nederlanders die een leven leiden buiten de grenzen van hun thuisland.

In elke aflevering praten we met inspirerende mensen die ons meenemen op een reis door hun persoonlijke ervaringen en uitdagingen, terwijl ze zich aanpassen aan nieuwe culturen en manieren van leven.

Van expats die werken bij multinationals tot digitale nomaden die de wereld rondreizen, we verkennen de verschillende manieren waarop mensen hun vleugels uitslaan en hun horizon verbreden. We bespreken niet alleen de opwinding en avonturen van het leven in het buitenland, maar ook de obstakels en het gevoel van heimwee dat soms opkomt.

Onze gasten zullen ons laten kennismaken met hun nieuwe thuisland, van de lokale gerechten en gewoonten tot de verschillende manieren van leven. We zullen ook bespreken hoe het is om ver van familie en vrienden te zijn en hoe ze deze afstand overbruggen.

Dus ga met ons mee op deze spannende reis en ontdek hoe het is om te leven en te werken buiten de grenzen van je eigen land. Abonneer je nu op Life Beyond Borders en mis geen enkele aflevering.

title: Testacoda. Conversazioni seriamente divertenti
description:
La vacanza è "dove posso fare le cose più

ovvie anche con le stampelle e la carrozzina". Va bene "un

week-end semplice, piccolo, libero, meraviglioso, a metà tra un

dono inatteso e un colpo di testa. Una folata di desiderio che

quando ci ripensi dici: ma è davvero successo? Che meraviglia!".

Enrica usa le stampelle, ma non smette di

desiderare le cose che ama solo perchè non cammina con le sue

gambe. "Ho una malattia complicata- racconta- ma la sclerosi

multipla non mi ha fatto un trapianto di personalità. Ho deciso

di non vivere in latitanza la mia disabilità, non sto bene in

casa", così parte.

Il suo viaggio è racchiuso in quasi 13 minuti di pura

emozione. Per mettersi in cammino con lei basta ascoltare

'Testacoda', il podcast scritto a quattro mani da due amici:

Enrica Marcenaro e Maurizio Orsola, pronti a raccontare in modo

divertente, ma non solo, un'avventura che parte dalla stazione

Termini.

Testacoda raccoglie, infatti, le conversazioni seriamente

divertenti di Enrica e Maurizio. Chiacchiere e battibecchi che

descrivono le loro esperienze sul vagone di un treno mentre

progettano una vacanza inclusiva che sia davvero libera per tutti

e due.

Per le persone come Enrica e Maurizio la libertà non deve

essere un sogno da lasciarsi alle spalle con rassegnazione; può

persino accadere che bisogna andare al contrario e fare qualche

"testacoda" per sentirsi liberi di essere e di fare. E con un pò

di ironia... Questa è una vera storia di viaggio e amicizia e

anche la destinazione della vacanza, "I Girasoli", è vera: è la

casa vacanze di Lucignano di Aism, Associazione italiana sclerosi

multipla.

Il montaggio e il mix di 'Testacoda' sono di Fabietto Crisante.

title: 胡言枫语 (Talk to Hu)
description:
天南地北的各位听众朋友，大家好，初次“见面”。我是主持人胡言，欢迎阅读胡言枫语的第0集，也就是我为本节目制作的序。向大家介绍一下，本播客名叫胡言枫语，枫是枫叶的枫，只因本播客在加拿大录制。我们是一档访谈类节目，主要是邀请其他与我一样在加拿大生活的华人朋友们一起从我们的视角聊聊大家感兴趣的话题，以及与海外生活相关的内容。我希望在这个节目中与邀请的嘉宾们能轻松愉快地聊天，聊天内容能够海纳百川，无所不谈。每期话题至少能邀请两个嘉宾，毕竟兼听则明，偏听则暗。以期能够听到一个话题从不同角度和立场出发而产生的探讨与意见碰撞。嘉宾们大多数也是我生活中的好朋友，他们来自各行各业，有着各自不同的生活与爱好。他们并不是什么专家学者，而是与你我一样一个个认真生活着的普通人，所以我们聊天的内容和观点理应是最真诚和真实的，能一定程度反映海外华人的所思所想。

简单介绍完了本节目，再稍微介绍一下本节目的制作人及主持人也就是我，胡言，大伙儿可以叫我老胡。我从来加拿大留学，到之后工作结婚已10年有余。我从小就是一个特别爱聊天的人，小时候在学校屡次因为话太多老师觉得我打扰了别人学习和休息而受到处罚。出国后，我又开始喜欢上看各种访谈节目，每当嘉宾们讨论的热火朝天时思维与意见的碰撞总是让我大呼过瘾，让我萌生了有一天也做主持人制作访谈节目的想法。近些年，我在各种网络冲浪时偶尔会观察到有时生活在中国的朋友们和海外的华人们偶尔会因为对彼此的不熟悉而互相产生误解，有时甚至排斥。于是我产生了做这么一档播客的想法。以期将我们海外华人方方面面的真实意见和想法表达传递出去。

最后向大家坦白。本人是第一次做主持人和播客。一切对我来说都是一个摸索学习的过程，如果有什么不妥的地方还望各位海涵，也欢迎各位的建议与指教。希望我能与这档播客一起进步，成熟。

以上就是序的所有内容。谢谢诸位的阅读。

It offers oversized, level, concrete sites, and caters to big rig setups. The park offers an abundance of amenities for it's guests, like, private showers, bathrooms and laundry facilities, kitchen facility, off-leash park, dog wash station, playground, pickleball court, gaga ball, EV stations and more.

Through the Camper Chicks podcast, Christa and Aneisa plan to bring you all the knowledge they have about full-time RV living and daily RV Park operations! What is JET? The Japan Exchange Teaching Program (JET) was started in 1987 as a grass roots effort to promote internationalization between the United States and Japan. Over 70,000 participants from 70+ countries (including 35,000 Americans) have been apart of this amazing experiment. JET's working as ALT's (Assistant Language Teachers), SEA's (Sports Exchange Advisors) or CIR's (Coordinator for International Relations) are cultural ambassadors helping to make positive and long lasting impacts and connections with Japanese people they meet and the communities they live in.

**This podcast is not officially endorsed by JET. The views and experiences expressed are solely those of guests.

Join Todd and Toddie, the dynamic father and son duo behind RCExcitement, as they dive into the fascinating world of RC (Radio Control) and share their personal stories of how this hobby has positively impacted their lives. In each episode, Todd and Toddie will explore various aspects of RC, from the excitement of building and customizing RC vehicles to the adrenaline rush of racing and competing. They'll also discuss the community aspect of RC, highlighting the friendships and connections they've made along the way. Whether you're a seasoned RC enthusiast or new to the hobby, "WhyRC" is the perfect podcast to deepen your understanding and appreciation for all things RC. Tune in as Todd and Toddie share their firsthand experiences, expert insights, and valuable tips that can enhance your RC journey. Expect engaging conversations, entertaining anecdotes, and heartfelt moments as this father and son duo share their passion for RC and explore the reasons why it holds a special place in their hearts. So, grab your favorite RC vehicle, sit back, and get ready for a thrilling ride with "WhyRC"! Don't forget to like, subscribe, and hit the notification bell to stay updated on all the latest episodes. Let's dive into the world of RC together!

title: Magic Ears
description:
Your enchanted audio gateway into the captivating world of Disney. Crafted for Disney lovers by Disney enthusiasts, our podcast explores every corner of the Disney universe, from theme parks and movies to mouthwatering snacks and unforgettable experiences.

A dual-segment podcast designed to cater to all your Disney interests. The first segment, 'Yummineers', takes your taste buds on a gastronomic journey through Disney's culinary universe. Our resident foodies review Disney snacks, dishes, and restaurants, bringing the magic of Disney dining right to your ears.

The second segment, 'The Waltineers Society', is your insider guide to all things Disney. Our knowledgeable hosts discuss everything Disney, from exhilarating theme park rides and spectacular events to beloved movies and shows. If it's part of the Disney realm, the 'Waltineers Society' is talking about it.

So, join us on 'Magic Ears', and let's experience the magic of Disney together. Whether you're a lifelong Disney aficionado or a new fan exploring the magic for the first time, 'Magic Ears' is your companion on this enchanting journey.

title: TimusTravelsPodcast!
description:
Welcome to the Timus Travels Podcast, where we embark on thrilling journeys, exploring the world one destination at a time! Join us as we delve into the wonders of cruising, car travel, and all-inclusive getaways, uncovering the secrets to creating unforgettable experiences.

In our podcast, we'll take you on a captivating voyage across the vast oceans as we discuss the magic of cruising. From breathtaking views of endless horizons to the luxurious amenities onboard, we'll guide you through various cruise lines, destinations, and must-try activities that cater to all types of travelers. Get ready to set sail and immerse yourself in the adventure of a lifetime.

If you prefer the freedom of the open road, we've got you covered! Our car travel episodes will ignite your wanderlust as we share road trip itineraries, hidden gems, and off-the-beaten-path attractions. Discover the joy of traversing scenic landscapes, stopping at charming towns, and indulging in delicious local cuisines. Whether you're a solo adventurer or traveling with friends and family, our podcast will inspire you to hit the road and create memories that will last a lifetime.

Looking for a stress-free vacation? Tune in as we unravel the world of all-inclusive resorts. From pristine beaches to opulent accommodations and a plethora of activities, we'll guide you through the top destinations where your every need is catered to. Dive into the crystal-clear waters, savor exquisite international cuisines, and experience unrivaled hospitality at these paradisiacal escapes.

In addition to destination highlights, Timus Travels Podcast will provide practical tips and tricks for travel planning, budgeting, packing, and making the most of your trips. Our expert guests will share their insights, recommendations, and stories, enriching your travel knowledge and inspiring you to step out of your comfort zone.

So, whether you're a seasoned explorer or a first-time adventurer, get ready to be captivated by the world of cruising, car travel, and all-inclusive vacations with Timus Travels Podcast. Let's set forth on a boundless expedition filled with laughter, excitement, and unforgettable moments. Happy travels!

Montevideo Sonoro. Un proyecto en constante construcción. Ciudad viva, en movimiento.

title: All Things Primitive
description:
Hosts James Parker and Randy Bevis discuss primitive living skills of our ancestors and learning the skills to get in touch with our primitive pasts.

James is a world class flint knapper, bowyer, primitive skills master from Gastonia, North Carolina. He is the owner of Huntworthy Productions. www.huuntworthyproductions.com.

Check out James extensive experience at https://www.huntworthyproductions.com/about-us

His wife Rebecca is an also a highly skilled maker of quill work items, basket weaving and primitive clothing. You can see examples of their work on the photo gallery https://www.huntworthyproductions.com/gallery

Randy also builds self bows and loved primitive bowhunting. He has lived overseas in Thailand for 20 years and travels to many counties that have interesting primitive skills histories of their own. Randy will share stories from these interesting places in podcasts as well.

Topics will include primitive skills living and include all aspects of the first primitive skills such as; Stone tools, fire making, cordage, shelters, hunting, tracking, foraging, food preparation and preservation, pottery, clothing and so on.

Cada podcast te llevaré a un viaje lleno de historias inspiradoras, consejos prácticos y conversaciones con expertos en turismo sostenible. Juntos, exploraremos cómo podemos disfrutar de nuestras aventuras mientras cuidamos de la belleza natural y cultural que Panamá ofrece.
